FAQ's
1. How can I contribute?
Register on our website redirectToHomePage(props)}>Bhasha Daan Choose a language - Assamese, Bangla, Gujarati, Hindi, Kannada, Malayalam, Manipuri, Marathi, Odia, Punjabi, Tamil, Telugu and Urdu. Handwrite the document provided and upload a good quality photograph of the handwritten document.
Which languages can I contribute to?
Assamese, Bangla, Gujarati, Hindi, Kannada, Malayalam, Manipuri, Marathi, Odia, Punjabi, Tamil, Telugu, Urdu.
Which languages can I contribute to?
Assamese, Bangla, Gujarati, Hindi, Kannada, Malayalam, Manipuri, Marathi, Odia, Punjabi, Tamil, Telugu, Urdu.
Who can volunteer?
Anyone with good knowledge of the language(s) mentioned above.
What happens if my handwritten document is rejected?
You can re-write and upload again.
Can I write with a pencil?
We prefer writing with a pen.
Do I need to include my name or any other personal information in the handwritten document?
No. Do not add any information other than what is being displayed to you to be written down.
Can I delete my uploaded file?
The files that are approved by the admin cannot be deleted.
My handwriting is not very good. Can I still write and upload?
Yes, we want a variety of data. You can write even if your handwriting is not very good. Make sure, the words are readable.
How old do I have to be to participate?
There are no age limitations, as long as you can read and write in the languages mentioned above.
Can I edit/correct already uploaded documents?
If the document is not approved by the admin, you can rewrite and upload.
Is there a limit to the number of documents that can be uploaded?
Only one photo per each text.
Can I contribute to more than one language?
Yes.
